<statement>
<image width="33%"  pi:generated="problems/images/6135acf8694c15bb54ff89463269064e.png" /><p>
Suppose a = 8 and b = 9. Calculate:</p>
<p>
c = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
A = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place. Give angles in <em>degrees</em>.
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>12.0</li><li>41.6</li><li>48.4</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={8}^{{2}}+{9}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={64}+{81}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={145}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}=\sqrt{{{145}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{12.041594578792}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{12}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle A</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arctan{{\left(\frac{{8}}{{9}}\right)}}}\approx{41.63353933657}\approx{41.6}</m></p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{B}={180}^{\circ}-{90}^{\circ}-{41.63353933657}^{\circ}\approx{48.36646066343}\approx{48.4}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

